Sources.AcquiringTips:
If acquiring this from Abalathian Wamoura, you may need to pull at least two enemies so that the Abalathian Wamoura has a target to cast Exuviation on.
Example: Pull a Window Wamoura along with an Abalathian Wamoura, then use Aqua Breath (or a similar spell that causes a debuff) on the Window Wamoura that entices the Abalathian Wamoura to cast Exuviation.

A party member is normally required if attempting to acquire it from Decaying Gourmand. If you get eaten, you will need an ally to get you out if you don't have any damage over time spells.
This spell can be obtained solo from Decaying Gourmand by reducing it to low HP, putting a damage over time effect on it, then being Devoured. So long as it gets the spell off, then dies from the DoT before killing you, you can learn it.

Sources.AcquiringTips: Ghrah Luminary will summon a monster called "Corruption". Killing the corruption is enough to obtain Aetheric Mimicry.

When the Mist Dragon begins casting Vaporize, it will summon 3 Draconic Regards (white dragon heads). You must leave at least one head alive in order for the cast to go off, otherwise the Mist Dragon will cast White Death instead and you will not get the spell.
Use Diamondback or other mitigation to help survive the damage.
Stotram is used early on as a party wide unavoidable attack that damages the party and heals adds, so nothing needs to be done to make it be cast.

This attack targets a different number of people throughout the fight with a marker and creates a large spotlight shining on the ground, exploding into light. The attack is guaranteed to happen early in the fight, so nothing needs to be done to make it be cast.
It's important to not get kidnapped by the ghosts when the Phantom Train is killed. If you are taken away by the ghost when the train dies, you will not acquire the ability.

This attack occurs midway through the Tokkapchi fight, so you may have to wait for it to cast it before killing it. Tokkapchi targets the Mud Slime it has periodically been creating during the fight (the one you should be managing the position of) with a cone shaped AoE attack.
Master Coeurl uses this immediately. Wait for it to finish casting before slaying it.
Coeurl Smriti casts it if both Coeurls don't die together.
Courser Chocobo will cast this after attacking a few times. Be sure to get out of the way as it can cause heavy damage!
